<p><a href="http://rolandtanglao.com/2020/07/29/p1-blogthis-checkvist-list-links-to-blog/">Discovered</a>: Nov 30, 2023 21:48 <a href="https://bigthink.com/high-culture/navajo-language/?utm_source=pocket-newtab-en-us">Why Navajo is one of the most difficult languages on Earth - Big Think</a> &lt;– I love human languages! So rich and complex! So great that Navajo has a future! –&gt; <strong>QUOTE</strong>: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">The Navajo, based in Arizona and New Mexico, separated from the Apache in the Middle Ages. Their language is intimidating for its tonality, complicated grammar, and concept of animacy, among other factors. Efforts to improve Navajo schooling can prevent the language — and culture — from dying out.</code></p>
